%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b829481dccedec948a42591ac1b2cd33, type: 3}
  m_Name: VernDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: KBTV.Runtime::KBTV.Dialogue.VernDialogueTemplate
  IntroductionLines:
  - Text: Alright night owls, we've got {callerName} on the line from {location}.
      What've you got for us tonight?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: '{callerName}, you''re on the air with Vern Castellano. The board''s lighting
      up tonight, so let''s hear it.'
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Next up, {callerName} calling in from {location}. Talk to me, friend.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Welcome to the show, {callerName}. You're live on KBTV. What's on your
      mind tonight?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Truth-seekers, we've got {callerName} joining us from {location}. Go ahead,
      caller.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ProbingLines:
  - Text: Alright, walk me through this. What exactly did you see out there?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: And when did this happen? Give me the details, don't leave anything out.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Hold on, slow down. Start from the beginning for the folks just tuning
      in.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Okay, I'm listening. Paint me a picture here.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Let's get specific. Time, location, what were you doing when this happened?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ExtraProbingLines:
  - Text: Now that's interesting. Tell me more about that last part.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: And what happened after that? Don't stop now.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Wait, back up. You said something there that caught my ear. Explain that
      again.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The listeners are gonna want to know - did anyone else see this?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Alright, I've got to ask - any physical evidence? Photos, recordings, anything?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  SkepticalLines:
  - Text: Now hold on a second there, friend. That could've been anything up there.
    Tone: 2
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I gotta be honest with you, I'm not buying it. Not yet anyway.
    Tone: 2
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You sure it wasn't just a plane? A satellite? Weather balloon maybe?
    Tone: 2
    Weight: 1
  - Text: See, I've been doing this a long time. I've heard a lot of stories. What
      makes yours different?
    Tone: 2
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I want to believe you, I really do. But you're gonna have to give me more
      than that.
    Tone: 2
    Weight: 1
  DismissiveLines:
  - Text: Yeah, okay. Thanks for calling in. Next caller.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Right. We're gonna move on. The board's lighting up and I've got real callers
      waiting.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Uh-huh. Appreciate it. Moving on.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Look, I've got a show to run here. Thanks for your time.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Alright, that's... that's enough of that. We'll be right back after these
      messages.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  BelievingLines:
  - Text: See, THIS is what I'm talking about, folks. This is why I do this show.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Now that's fascinating. I believe you. I really do.
    Tone: 5
    Weight: 1
  - Text: This is exactly the kind of call I live for, night owls. You hearing this?
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You know what? Your voice tells me everything I need to know. You're telling
      the truth.
    Tone: 5
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Folks, write this down. Mark the date. We're witnessing something here
      tonight.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  TiredLines:
  - Text: Mm-hmm... go on.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Alright... what else? *yawn* Sorry, long night.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Yeah... okay... I'm with you.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Keep going. Just need another coffee here...
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Right, right... what time is it? Never mind, continue.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  AnnoyedLines:
  - Text: Get to the point, caller. The clock's ticking.
    Tone: 6
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We don't have all night here. Well, we do, but I'd like to talk to more
      than one person.
    Tone: 6
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Is there a point to this story? Because I'm losing the thread here.
    Tone: 6
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Look, I've got a board full of callers. You gonna give me something or
      not?
    Tone: 6
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'm gonna stop you right there. Where is this going?
    Tone: 6
    Weight: 1
  EngagingLines:
  - Text: Oh, is that right? Well, let's hear more about this adventure of yours.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Ha! You know what, I appreciate the creativity here. Keep going.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Sure, sure. And what else happened in this totally real encounter?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Look, the listeners at home are entertained, so let's ride this out.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You're pulling my leg, but you know what? It's late, I'll play along.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  CutOffLines:
  - Text: Alright, we're gonna have to cut you off there. Thanks for calling.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'm gonna stop you right there. We've got other callers waiting. Appreciate
      it.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Yeah, that's all the time we've got for this one, folks. Moving on.
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We need to take a break. Thanks for calling in. *click*
    Tone: 4
    Weight: 1
  - Text: And on that note, let's go to the next caller. Keep watching the skies.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  SignOffLines:
  - Text: Appreciate the call, {callerName}. Keep watching the skies out there.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Thanks for sharing that with us tonight. Stay vigilant, truth-seeker.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Stay safe out there, {callerName}. And keep those eyes on the horizon.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Powerful stuff, {callerName}. Thanks for having the courage to share it.
    Tone: 5
    Weight: 1
  - Text: That's what this show is all about, folks. Thanks for the call. We'll be
      right back.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ShowOpeningLines:
  - Text: Good evening, truth-seekers. You're tuned to KBTV, Beyond the Veil AM.
      I'm your host, Vern Castellano, and we've got a big show for you tonight.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: It's midnight on the dial, and you know what that means. Welcome to KBTV.
      The phone lines are open, and the truth is out there waiting.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Welcome back, night owls. This is Vern Castellano coming to you live from
      the KBTV studios. Tonight, we're going deep.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You're listening to KBTV, where we pull back the curtain on what they don't
      want you to know. Let's get started.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The witching hour approaches, and so do the callers. This is KBTV. I'm
      Vern. Let's see what's out there tonight.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ShowClosingLines:
  - Text: And that's all the time we have tonight, folks. Thanks to everyone who
      called in. Keep watching the skies.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The sun's coming up, truth-seekers. Time to sign off. But remember - the
      truth doesn't sleep, and neither should you.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: That's a wrap on tonight's show. This is Vern Castellano saying goodnight,
      and stay vigilant out there.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We're out of time, but never out of mysteries. Thanks for listening to
      KBTV. Until next time.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Another night, another pile of evidence. Thanks for being part of the search,
      folks. This is KBTV, signing off.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  BetweenCallersLines:
  - Text: Fascinating stuff. Let's see who else is on the line.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Alright, we've got more callers waiting. Let's keep this going.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The board's lighting up tonight. Let's go to our next caller.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Interesting call. But we've got more stories to hear. Next caller, you're
      on.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: That's what I love about this show - you never know what's coming next.
      Speaking of which...
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The lines are burning up tonight. Let's keep the momentum going.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: More callers in the queue. Let's see what else is out there.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Alright, next up on the lines...
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Good stuff. We've got more waiting in the wings.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: That's the kind of call that keeps me coming back every night. Who's next?
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  DeadAirFillerLines:
  - Text: Phone lines are quiet for the moment. If you've got a story, now's the
      time to call in.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We're waiting on callers, folks. Don't be shy. The number's on your screen.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You know, nights like this give me time to think about all the stories
      we've heard over the years...
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Quiet on the lines. That's unusual. Makes you wonder what's keeping people
      up tonight.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: While we wait for callers, let me tell you - I've seen some things in my
      years doing this show.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The truth doesn't call itself in, folks. Someone out there has a story.
      I can feel it.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Empty lines. Either everyone's asleep or everyone's seen something and
      they're too scared to talk.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: If you're just tuning in, this is KBTV. We're here all night, and we want
      to hear from you.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Come on, night owls. Don't leave me hanging here. What's happening out
      there?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Slow night on the lines. But that's alright. The best calls always come
      when you least expect them.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  DroppedCallerLines:
  - Text: Looks like we lost that caller. Phone lines, am I right?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: And... they're gone. Technical difficulties, folks. Let's move on.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Hello? You still there? Guess not. Next caller.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We lost 'em. Happens sometimes. The truth doesn't always have a good signal.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Caller dropped. Either bad reception or... well, let's not speculate.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
